title: Japan Terms of Trade
description: Terms of Trade in Japan increased to 70.70 points in October from 70.10 points in September of 2022. Terms of Trade in Japan averaged 161.83 points from 1960 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 276.10 points in August of 1960 and a record low of 70.10 points in September of 2022. In Japan, Terms of Trade (ToT) correspond to the ratio of Price of exportable goods to the Price of importable goods. This page provides - Japan Terms of Trade - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank of Japan
